news.title: Punjab housing department issues clearance certificates to 51 builders
news.para: Housing and urban development minister Hardeep Singh Mundian and chief secretary KAP Sinha handed over colony licences, completion certificates, partial completion certificates, letters of intent, zoning plans, building plans, promoter registration certificates and lay-out plans to 51 builders.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body's CCTV mandate faces objections from builders
news.para: ​​Under AMC's ‘Good Construction Practices' to reduce air pollution, sites over 10,000 sq m were directed to install CCTV cameras and air quality sensor.

news.title: Oberoi Realty raises Rs 1,500 crore through issuance of non-convertible debentures
news.para: Recently, Oberoi Realty's board had considered and approved the proposal for enabling raising of funds for an aggregate amount not exceeding Rs 6,000 crore.

news.title: ED interrogates former CEO of Noida authority in Hacienda projects scam
news.para: The former officer, along with promoters and directors of Hacienda Projects Private Limited (HPPL), is accused of a scam worth Rs 636 crore.

news.title: China to boost credit and help renovate one million homes
news.para: At a briefing on Thursday, Housing Minister Ni Hong offered fresh help, saying Beijing will "increase the credit scale of white-list projects to four trillion" yuan ($562 billion) by the end of the year.

news.title: New Delhi civic body imposes Rs 50,000 fine for dust pollution at construction sites
news.para: Due to sustained poor Air Quality Index (AQI) for the past few days in Delhi, the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) Stage 1 was implemented on Tuesday.

news.title: Sebi to auction 27 properties of Rose Valley group worth Rs 63.26 crore on November 25
news.para: The properties to go under the hammer include flats, buildings, land parcels and hotels located in West Bengal and Bihar, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in a notice.

news.title: Capital India sells housing finance subsidiary to Weaver Services for Rs 267 crore
news.para: To finance this acquisition, WEAVER is raising capital from leading private equity funds including Gaja Capital and Lok Capital to secure up to Rs 800 crore in funding according to a release by the company.

news.title: ADIA's Lake Shore raises Rs 1,200 crore green loan for Viviana mall in Thane
news.para: The integrated institutional investor has raised the funds through Lake Shore Group entity Salsette Developers that owns the retail property in Thane. HSBC Commercial Banking has provided the loan that was used to refinance the existing lenders and provide liquidity to the company.

news.title: Bollywood actor Sara Ali Khan buys two office properties in Mumbai’s Andheri
news.para: Sara Ali Khan and her mother, Amrita Singh, have purchased two office spaces totaling nearly 4,200 sq ft in Mumbai’s Andheri locality for over Rs 22.26 crores. The offices are located on the 9th floor of a commercial project by Veer Savarkar Projects. Real estate remains a favored investment among Bollywood celebrities.

news.title: Authum, Kotak, others file initial bids for Lavasa Corporation
news.para: Creditors have extended the timeline to submit expressions of interest to October 24 after requests from three more parties. Creditors have also put to vote a proposal to replace Deloitte-backed resolution professional (RP) Shailesh Verma with Udayraj Patwardhan who will be supported by EY.

news.title: Navi Mumbai police file case against four for cheating interior designer in land deal
news.para: The accused persons sold a piece of land at Pali in Raigad district to the 46-year-old victim for Rs 68.10 lakh, but failed to deliver possession of the property

news.title: Gross leasing of office space to cross 80 million sq ft across eight cities in 2024: Report
news.para: The gross leasing of office space rose 66 per cent to 24.8 million square feet across the top eight cities in Q3 2024, marking the second highest quarterly leasing volume in the sector's history.

news.title: Bhaane Retail buys South Mumbai’s Rhythm House through insolvency auction
news.para: In February 2020, the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) ordered the liquidation of Rhythm House, which had been seized by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) in 2018 during its investigation into the Punjab National Bank scam involving Modi.

news.title: Delhi LG approves land acquisition for Aerocity-Tughlakabad metro corridor
news.para: Delhi Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena has approved the acquisition of land measuring 1,688 square metre at Khanpur Village in south Delhi, they said.

news.title: Mysore development body set to resume site auctions
news.para: Muda, having acquired 14 sites relinquished by chief minister Siddaramaiah's wife, Parvathi, will also auction these sites, but only after the culmination of the ongoing inquiry into the alleged scam.

news.title: Sebi to auction 15 properties of five companies on November 19
news.para: The move is part of Sebi's efforts to recover money collected by these companies from investors in violation of norms. Properties that will go under the hammer including flats, land with structure and land parcels are located in West Bengal and Odisha.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to blacklist Sanghani Infrastructure for delays in Thaltej housing project
news.para: The civic body has now decided to blacklist Sanghani Infrastructure India Pvt Ltd for five years, a proposal for which was presented at the housing committee meeting on Oct 16.

news.title: Maharashtra: Property registrations to be disrupted from October 18-21 due to system upgrade
news.para: Up to 13,000 properties are registered in the state every day. "The upgrade in the Government Receipt Accounting System (GRAS) was to be carried out last week, but postponed owing to Dasara festivities.

news.title: Ahmedabad development body refunds excess charges to developers in Bopal TP schemes
news.para: ​​These charges were levied in cases where Auda could not deduct the entire 40% land as mandated under the Town Planning Act. The lesser deductions had happened since development had already taken place on some under the Bopal TP schemes 1,2 and 3.
